      • addDomain

        public void addDomain​(long address,
                      int ownerID,
                      int[] spanIDs,
                      long groupAddress,
                      long childAddress,
                      long parentAddress)
        Allows to add a domain with the variables obtainable from load_balance(int this_cpu, struct rq *this_rq, struct sched_domain *sd).
        Parameters:
        address - the memory address of current struct, for linking purpose.
        ownerID - the id of cpu owning this domain.
        spanIDs - the id of cpus involved in this domain.
        groupAddress - the memory address of the first group in the circular list, for linking purpose.
        childAddress - the memory address of child domain, for linking purpose.
        parentAddress - the memory address of parent domain, for linking purpose.

      • addGroup

        public void addGroup​(long address,
                     int[] membersID,
                     long nextGroupAddress)
        Allows to add a group with the variables obtainable from load_balance(int this_cpu, struct rq *this_rq, struct sched_domain *sd).
        Parameters:
        address - the memory address of current struct, for linking purpose.
        membersID - the ids of the member cpus.
        nextGroupAddress - the memory address of the next group in the circular list, for linking purpose.

      • build

        public SchedDomains build()
                   throws LinkException
        Create a SchedDomains from the stored objects and links.
        Returns:
        Called after the addition of all required objects, returns a valid SchedDomains.
        Throws:
        LinkException - if there are missing objects or invalid parent-child link.

      • getGroupsAddresses

        public Collection<Long> getGroupsAddresses()
